ground-tie
Homonym Number:
Word Class: verb
Sense Number:  1
Definition:[saddle horses] to stand and wait for riders, while reins are left lying on the ground.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
