Source:  Practical Guide to Handling Dogs and Stock
Author:  MILLS ET AL
Vol / Page:  65
Edition:
Quote:  If you have any horse-training ideas (I dislike the term horse-breaking, which often literally means just that) always teach your young horse to 'ground-tie' - in other words to stay put once the reins are thrown over its head.
